@bossgirlbujo shares this great technique for business owners or anyone who doesn't want to get caught up in certain tasks. Power Hour!
She says: "I'm always on the lookout for new #productivity hacks.  I was inspired recently by @allison_hardy_ She uses a #powerhour technique to quickly get through important tasks that move her business forward, but are also tasks that can quickly become a time suck.

Here's how it works:
Pick 6 important tasks and do them the first hour of your day, spending only 10 minutes on each one.

I loved the idea so much, I decided to bookend my days with power hours.  I have six tasks I do first thing in the morning, and six tasks I do at the end of my work day. I'm really liking it because it gets some of those small tasks off my plate early in the day, so they aren't nagging at the back of my mind.  At the end of the day, it signifies that my work day is done and I can unplug and focus on my family.

You'll see that email is included.  I get a lot of email and there's no way I can get through it in only 10 minutes, but that amount of time allows me to glance through and see if there's anything that needs immediate attention.  If I see a task that will take more than a minute or two, I write it in my #bulletjournal and take care of it later in the day.

I've also included checking in on Facebook and Instagram.  I've been feeling overwhelmed lately, and I think being online so much is part of the problem.  So I've really been trying to limit the time I spend.  We'll see how long I can spend only 10 minutes twice a day, but for now, it's going well and feels like a much-needed break."
